  _________________________________________________________________________
                                                 SmallBASIC IDE for Console
                                                 
  Platform notes:
  >> on Linux, shift+movement keys are used by console/xterm
  
  Cursor keys			Movement
  Home					Jump to begin of line  
  Home+Home				Previous page								(brief)
  Home+Home+Home		Jump to begin of file						(brief)
  End					Jump to end of line 
  End+End				Next page								    (brief)
  End+End+End			Jump to end of file							(brief)

  Alt+G					Go to line									(brief)
  Alt+1..9				Set bookmark [1..9] to current position		(brief)
  Alt+J					Jump to bookmark							(brief)
   
  Delete				Deletes block or the next character
  NumPad Delete			(the same as Delete)
  Backspace				Deletes block or the previous character
  Alt+K					Delete to end-of-line					(dos,brief)
  
  Alt+D/Ctrl+Y			Delete line							(dos,brief,joe)
  
  Ctrl+Z				Undo										  (win)
  NumPad */Alt+U		Undo										(brief)
  Alt+*					Same as NumPad - (good for xterm w/o numpad)
  
  NumPad 5				Center to screen
  Ctrl+L				Redraw screen
  _________________________________________________________________________
                                                                    Generic
  F5,Ctrl+F				Search 								(dos,win,brief)
  						In the prompt, enter < as first character to search
  						backward, > or none to search forward.
  
  F3,Ctrl+N,Shift+F5	Find next							(dos,win,brief)

  Ctrl+P				Find previous
  _________________________________________________________________________
                                                             Find & Replace  
  Alt+I					Toggles overwrite/insert mode
  Ctrl+A				Toggle auto-indent mode
  _________________________________________________________________________
                                                                       Mode
  Alt+M					Simple selection (also, shift+movement keys)(brief)
  Shift+Cursor keys/PgDn/PgUp/Home/End (same as Alt+M)			  (dos,win)
  
  Alt+L					Line selection								(brief)
  
  NumPad -				Cut or line-cut if no selection				(brief)
  Alt+-					Same as NumPad - (good for xterm w/o numpad)
  NumPad + 				Copy or line-copy if no selection			(brief)
  Alt+=					Same as NumPad + (good for xterm w/o numpad)
  Insert				Paste										(brief)

  Ctrl+C				Copy or line-copy if no selection		  (dos,win)
  Ctrl+V				Paste									  (dos,win)
  Ctrl+X				Cut or line-cut if no selection			  (dos,win)
  _________________________________________________________________________
                                                                  Clipboard  
  Alt+E					Edit file (open file)						(brief)
  Alt+O					Change filename (rename file)				(brief)
  Alt+W					Save										(brief)
  Alt+X					Exit									(dos,brief)
  Alt+B					Select buffer (files)						(brief)
  Alt+P					Previous buffer								(brief)
  Alt+N					Next buffer									(brief)
  _________________________________________________________________________
                                                              Files/Buffers
  F11					Save & compile
  						The result will be stored on ~/.output buffer
  						
  F12					Save, compile & run
  						Compiler's output will be stored on ~/.output
  						buffer
  						
  F1/Alt+H				Keyword search (keyword on cursor)
  _________________________________________________________________________
                                                       Compiler/interpreter
  Shift+F1				This screen
  F9					Macros prompt
  F10					Command prompt
